subSubSection.paragraph:
P. maroccana

occurs in the same region and sometimes together with 

P. borreyi
.

It is easily recognized by its brown base colour (dark grey to black in 

P. borreyi

), the broad and short discal spot on the hindwing (usually smaller and longer in 

P. borreyi

), the white subapical spot on the antenna of the male (absent in 

P. borreyi

) and the shape of the PTA (see also 
Kallies 1999
).
